get.summary:
The auth-code login callback (kick / twitter). The literal `twitch/callback` route wins for Twitch;
this handles every other provider, exchanging the code with the stored PKCE verifier into a session and
responding per the client class (mobile deep-link / served-web fragment+cookie / JSON).

BanUserRequest.description:
A dashboard ban request (chat-client.md §3.5). string BanUserRequest.Scope is `"this_channel"` (default) or
`"all_moderated"`. A int? BanUserRequest.DurationSeconds turns a `this_channel` action into a timeout;
`all_moderated` is always a permanent ban across every channel Twitch says the operator moderates.

SeTimer.description:
A StreamElements timer. SE stores the recurrence as an `Interval` in SECONDS and a minimum
`ChatLines` activity gate. A timer may carry either a single `Message` or a `Messages` list;
both are accepted and merged on import.

TwitchPrediction.description:
A Channel Points Prediction. string? TwitchPrediction.WinningOutcomeId is empty until the prediction resolves;
DateTimeOffset? TwitchPrediction.EndedAt and DateTimeOffset? TwitchPrediction.LockedAt are null until those transitions occur. Returned by
Get / Create / End Prediction.
